@* THE CONTROL FOR decision 167, AND IT IS THE SAME FILE ONE ATTRIBUTE SHORTER.

   Character for character Unsupported/Gate/CascadeIsFixed.razor without ` IsFixed="true"`. It
   compiles clean, so the refusal next door is located on IsFixed and on NOTHING else -- not on the
   two consumers under one cascade, not on GaugeB's bound Tag, not on the shape of the markup.

   It is also the WORKAROUND the diagnostic names: dropping IsFixed leaves a live cascade, which is
   the one measured against Blazor by the 'cascade' contract (BENCH n°53) and costs nothing to keep.

   VALID BLAZOR: dotnet build of this source in a real Blazor WebAssembly project succeeds. *@
<div id="wrap"><CascadingValue Value="@level"><GaugeA Tag="static" /><GaugeB Tag="@tick" /></CascadingValue><button id="inc" @onclick="Inc">inc</button></div>

@code {
    private int level = 1;
    private string tick = "t";
    void Inc() { level++; tick = tick + "!"; }
}
